{
  "stem": "19550.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It must have been chicory, sometimes a little more sweet, sometimes less sweet, in the morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in the evening, there would be a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think it was 20 grams.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And some kind of slop that was called soup, which some time consisted of some potato peels or little pieces of some vegetable.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, this is-- it's all a very complicated story that-- like everything about the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The bread, you know, was obviously spiked, and certainly in the later days, with sawdust.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The soups were really slop.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was, in labor camps, there was supposed to have been at least some residue of meat in it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you have to know that although Germany was a very orderly and well-organized country, their human systems are very imperfect.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there was plenty of corruption, particularly at that let slay-- late stage in the war for a whole variety of reasons, political and practical.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the most practical reason was that the Germans also were lacking quite a bit of everything.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so the-- the SS were stealing the camps blind from whatever monies that they were supplied with, or what they were collecting as payment.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were hired out to other institutions and structures in the Nazi state.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they collected whatever they collected for us, and then they supposedly administered and operated the camps out of it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were stealing, as they were stealing from the food supply that was destined toward the-- for the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] You know, these-- there is no way in which [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] anything about the camps or the Holocaust can be adequately described.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Let me really say this.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
